parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Seat Belt Lock-Up and Failure to Release
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belts to release can lead to accidents or injuries due to the inability to properly restrain occupants, especially in the event of sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: The front seat belts lock up and do not release
the belts tighten excessively
the belts do not extract from the retractor
the belts are stuck in the retracted position
and the belts are unable to be used.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belts to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries due to the inability to properly restrain occupants.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor fails to extract the belt
the belt is stuck in the retracted position
and the belt is unable to be used.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt timing module can cause the seat belts to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries due to the inability to properly restrain occupants.
symptoms: The seat belt timing module fails to function properly
causing the belts to lock up or fail to release.
